TY  - JOUR
T1  - Robust Predictions in Games With Incomplete Information
AU  - Bergemann, Dirk
AU  - Morris, Stephen
Y1  - 2013/07/01
PY  - 2013
DA  - 2013/07/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA11105
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 1251
EP  - 1308
VL  - 81
IS  - 4
KW  - Incomplete information
KW  - correlated equilibrium
KW  - robustness to private information
KW  - moment restrictions
KW  - identification
KW  - information bounds
KW  - linear best responses
KW  - quadratic payoffs
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA11105
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We analyze games of incomplete information and offer equilibrium predictions that are valid for, and in this sense robust to, all possible private information structures that the agents may have. The set of outcomes that can arise in equilibrium for some information structure is equal to the set of Bayes correlated equilibria. We completely characterize the set of Bayes correlated equilibria in a class of games with quadratic payoffs and normally distributed uncertainty in terms of restrictions on the first and second moments of the equilibrium action?state distribution. We derive exact bounds on how prior knowledge about the private information refines the set of equilibrium predictions. We consider information sharing among firms under demand uncertainty and find new optimal information policies via the Bayes correlated equilibria. We also reverse the perspective and investigate the identification problem under concerns for robustness to private information. The presence of private information leads to set rather than point identification of the structural parameters of the game.
ER  - 

